  "_goal_comment": "Second composition axis: the tenant's GOAL / traffic source (plans/LANDING_PAGE_GOAL_COMPOSITION.md). A goal enables capability PACKS on top of the offer_type base \u2014 never a hand-maintained offer_type x goal matrix. Packs are union-only: they add, never remove, so a page with no goal composes exactly as it did before goals existed (no migration). A pack has two halves because the two kinds of section behave differently. `seeds` are content-bearing body elements (faq, testimonials, ...) that render nothing until a tenant fills them in \u2014 the create wizard seeds them as empty scaffolds into builder state and they are tenant-owned from then on, so changing goal never deletes copy. `sections` are governed sections the goal turns on; that suits DERIVED head/sidecar output (structured_data, llms_txt) needing no tenant input, and is empty until those exist (Phase 3) \u2014 the mechanism is here so they slot in without a renderer change. Editing guide: docs/CONFIGURING_GOALS.md. NEVER delete or rename a goal \u2014 pages that stored it would stop validating and could no longer be saved or re-rendered. Retire one with \"deprecated\": true, which hides it from the wizard while existing pages keep validating and composing.",
  "packs": {
    "discoverability": { "label": "Discoverability", "seeds": ["faq"], "sections": ["structured_data"] },
    "social_proof":    { "label": "Social proof",    "seeds": ["testimonials", "rating", "client_marquee"], "sections": [] }
  },
  "goals": {
    "paid_ads":   { "label": "Paid ads",     "note": "Ad traffic converts fast or bounces. Adds nothing extra \u2014 no FAQ, no SEO weight.", "packs": [] },
    "search_seo": { "label": "Search / SEO", "note": "Built to rank: adds an FAQ, and (later) structured data and llms.txt derived from the offer.", "packs": ["discoverability"] },
    "social":     { "label": "Social",       "note": "Built to convert a scrolling audience: adds social proof \u2014 testimonials, rating, client logos.", "packs": ["social_proof"] },
    "email_list": { "label": "Email list",   "note": "A warm audience that already knows you. Adds nothing extra \u2014 straight to the offer.", "packs": [] },
    "minimal":    { "label": "Minimal",      "note": "No extras of any kind. The offer's standard page, with nothing added on top.", "packs": [] }
  }
